# Dice Roller

Command-line dice rolling simulator built with Python.

## Overview

This project allows users to roll one or more dice with a custom number of sides. The program generates random results, displays each roll in a clean format, and lets the user continue rolling until they choose to quit.

## Project Files

- [View Dice Roller Source Code](./Dice_Roller.py)

## Features

- Choose the number of dice
- Choose the number of sides per die
- Generate random roll results
- Roll again until the user quits
- Display results in a clean command-line format

